cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI

The paper presents a method for automatic identification of individual animals based on their vocal sounds, which involves machine learning and data analysis techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Among these, cs.SD and cs.SI are the most likely categories as they directly relate to the study of animal vocalizations and their social implications. cs.CL is also a likely category as it involves the use of natural language processing techniques for analyzing animal sounds. cs.LG and cs.AI are less likely categories, but still relevant as they deal with the development of machine learning algorithms for classification and recognition tasks.
